    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03197.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="bottom">from Editor <hi rend="underline">Nineteenth Century</hi></note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Queen Anne's Lodge,</name>
                    <name type="place">St James's Park. S. W.</name>
                    <date when="1884-08-20"><hi rend="underline">20th Aug 1884</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir /</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am very much obliged by your kind offer of the little <choice><abbr>M.S.</abbr><expan>manuscript</expan></choice> on "What lurks behind
                Shakespeare's Historical Plays?" &#38; greatly regret that its extreme brevity renders
                it hardly suitable as an article for the XIX<hi rend="superscript"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Century.</p>
            <p>I return it accordingly herewith but in the hope that you may see your way to amplify
                the treatment beyond its present limits of a mere hint or suggestion, &#38; give it
                the importance by way of illustration &#38; proof which the subject deserves. Hoping
                to hear again from you &#38; thanking you cordially for writing to me at all, I remain
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">James Knowles</hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p><hi rend="underline">Walt Whitman Esq</hi></p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
